The method we used to measure the porosity (P) of the porous silicon layer was based on the weight measurement of the mass of the specimen before (original mass, m0) and after (m1) anodization and the mass (m2) after merely removing the porous layer. The porosity can be obtained by the equation:p=m0−m1m0−m2\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
